Basidiospores of three newly-described species. 
<emphasis id="178B552A70E42FE6385F4A27914E8357" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">a</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="D2040D5F9878496C1F997910B892B172" authorityName="Y. Li &amp; M. L. Xie" authorityYear="2020" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cortinarius laccariphyllus" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="laccariphyllus">
<emphasis id="AD7D469C45CF9F929315CB697B86DCEC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Cortinarius laccariphyllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(HMJAU44449, holotype); 
<emphasis id="41AD0D8CA4894FA50BF539BC0ABB4DDB" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">b</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="1B553669759B3C65F9F97E94631FD496" authorityName="Y. Li, M. L. Xie &amp; T. Z. Wei" authorityYear="2020" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cortinarius neotorvus" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="neotorvus">
<emphasis id="EA8AD95669241EF17CBB96C635D9628E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Cortinarius neotorvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(HMJAU44441, holotype); 
<emphasis id="1567889AB0EF368847AA9A548B30974B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">c</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="D0ED4EBB495385987615A76F88C1B7A2" authorityName="Y. Li &amp; M. L. Xie" authorityYear="2020" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cortinarius subfuscoperonatus" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="subfuscoperonatus">
<emphasis id="5C019C1AA50BEC11EE04AEAC367E56F3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Cortinarius subfuscoperonatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(HMJAU44444, holotype). Photographs by Meng-Le Xie.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5D9EAEBAEBE41F9072B5ACE311E57427" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" type="its sequence">
<paragraph id="7622CE4A9E1470C4E258FDD3C0590C89" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">ITS sequence.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9A6C74454B1CFBDB9EBDFED0FF235BC3" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">
The ITS sequences of 
<taxonomicName id="62DE69637D555A000FE52B394D1A2137" genus="C." lsidName="C. neotorvus" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" rank="species" species="neotorvus">
<emphasis id="409F3797309EC99F504D61A4FA9EDA59" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">C. neotorvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are 513-515 bp long (5 collections, Table 
<tableCitation id="F06424BC1F81960396AE8CE475D6D3C0" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. ITS sequences used in the phylogenetic analysis. New species in bold." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/69D64390F941E77797A9483FB02F05D6" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" tableUuid="69D64390F941E77797A9483FB02F05D6">1</tableCitation>
). All four sequences (MK552384 holotype, MK552385, MK552386 and MK552382) are identical and only MK552383 has 2 bp indels. The ITS sequence of 
<taxonomicName id="D26A67CF3CE664902DBD54CA5C8F160D" genus="C." lsidName="C. neotorvus" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" rank="species" species="neotorvus">
<emphasis id="B729578BD4165D6B7EC67EA0887805CB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">C. neotorvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MK552384, holotype) differs from the sequences of other species in section 
<taxonomicName id="06A4D9DCDF3DEC35400B177294DFAA3C" genus="C." lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" rank="section" section="Telamonia">Telamonia</taxonomicName>
by at least six substitutions and five indels.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="29A98ADB121B1F113FB4F886C0C82AF7" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="1E416AAC8227F001F6864A28A1E9D306" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Ecology and distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF2DE00E00098785EB02BEEF3CAB729E" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">
In broadleaf forest (
<taxonomicName id="0AB687947E97C764A25D1A40364FFFFA" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Quercus mongolica" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mongolica">
<emphasis id="51FAF5F55F2D59CFA95FC8E6ED9CF5EA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Quercus mongolica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
dominated forest). Solitary or gregarious. Known from Jilin and Heilongjiang Province, China.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
