<subSubSection id="83BFB25481912D7C4E3F51C80DB4895C" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" type="comments">
<paragraph id="2EE6B6A190A44BA3C24182796E7195DB" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B2E33F210339BEFB899D2EC0FB6BB48A" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">
<taxonomicName id="4083E569084FE25177D25C953A4B5214" authorityName="Y. Li, M. L. Xie &amp; T. Z. Wei" authorityYear="2020" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cortinarius neotorvus" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="neotorvus">
<emphasis id="5973A32A0BDA91D11A8EAB3AA6E7B517" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Cortinarius neotorvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily confused with 
<taxonomicName id="781AEE7D147CBAF0E6EA6AD3069A65E7" genus="C." lsidName="C. torvus" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" rank="species" species="torvus">
<emphasis id="8420B3AF9EF3DF0FBBB0437155567A79" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">C. torvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to highly similar morphology. Morphologically, the lamellae of 
<taxonomicName id="6017D1D73B7702FF2BDE417615357019" genus="C." lsidName="C. torvus" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" rank="species" species="torvus">
<emphasis id="A2CADFC7775E8241BFEAEB903ABDCD15" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">C. torvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are adnate to subdecurrent and distant (
<bibRefCitation id="86EE5CFE4C6F6C404C1FAE138612C091" author="Bidaud, A" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" refId="B7" refString="Bidaud, A, Moenne-Loccoz, P, Reumaux, P, Henry, R, 1999. Atlas des Cortinaires IX. Editions Federation Mycologique Dauphine-Savoie, Meyzieu." title="Atlas des Cortinaires IX. Editions Federation Mycologique Dauphine-Savoie, Meyzieu." year="1999">Bidaud et al. 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="2749CAA718B13B5B6E8BF77EE1B494A0" author="Breitenbach, J" journalOrPublisher="Mycological Progress" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" refId="B14" refString="Breitenbach, J, Kraenzlin, F, 2000. Fungi of Switzerland. Vol. 5 Agarics (3rd part) Cortinariaceae. Mycologia Luzern, Lucerna." title="Fungi of Switzerland. Vol. 5 Agarics (3 rd part) Cortinariaceae. Mycologia Luzern, Lucerna." year="2000">
Breitenbach and 
<normalizedToken id="518EDC7E3E7CA2A4D1559385E1DD00F8" originalValue="Kränzlin">Kraenzlin</normalizedToken>
2000
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="439FBD289348ECCF34D06C3E0E871AF2" author="Soop, K" journalOrPublisher="New Zealand Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" refId="B50" refString="Soop, K, 2014. Cortinarius in Sweden (14 edition). Editions Scientrixk, Sweden." title="Cortinarius in Sweden (14 edition). Editions Scientrixk, Sweden." year="2014">Soop 2014</bibRefCitation>
) and the pileus colour of 
<taxonomicName id="6DDD4C29DB804F9DAF6AD612591B7EC3" genus="C." lsidName="C. torvus" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" rank="species" species="torvus">
<emphasis id="3ED3300F8F31CB5A1B02DF83539635D8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">C. torvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is usually darker and with a violet tinge, as well as the stipe usually being bulbous at the base (
<bibRefCitation id="ABD6BE11736386E69C4C98EAF7F35D6F" author="Consiglio, G" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Fungal Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" refId="B16" refString="Consiglio, G, Antonini, D, Antonini, M, 2003. Il Genere Cortinarius in Italia (Parte prima). Associazione Micologica Bresadola, Luglio." title="Il Genere Cortinarius in Italia (Parte prima). Associazione Micologica Bresadola, Luglio." year="2003">Consiglio et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
). In molecular data, the ITS sequence of 
<taxonomicName id="793C9B9B9F57195FCB69753BE8011ABC" genus="C." lsidName="C. neotorvus" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" rank="species" species="neotorvus">
<emphasis id="16BCE43C02C0B811973EADBB7E612BBD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">C. neotorvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MK552384, holotype) differ from the sequences of 
<taxonomicName id="521375A2559386B7D05FE29FA5D56154" genus="C." lsidName="C. torvus" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" rank="species" species="torvus">
<emphasis id="018B1225AD091EE2FC8B01CE002396D8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">C. torvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(AY669668, JX407337) by six substitutions and five indels. In the phylogenetic analyses, the five specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="29CF0016F4CE800F605CD13C30FD89DA" genus="C." lsidName="C. neotorvus" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" rank="species" species="neotorvus">
<emphasis id="57250DA90EAE7C4F49DBEA12204738BC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">C. neotorvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were placed in separate monophyletic lineages (BPP = 0.96, MLBS = 90%) and formed a sister relationship with 
<taxonomicName id="AA45C74539D471396595D320A8124E16" genus="C." lsidName="C. torvus" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" rank="species" species="torvus">
<emphasis id="FA3E6338B351D5FB3A7656D2314CFE6B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">C. torvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
